# JQueryValidation

Provides forms with jquery.validation functionality.

## Usage
Start up validation to a give form like this:

	$form = new Form(
		$this,
		'Form',
		$fields,
		new FieldList(
			new FormAction(
				'FormHandler',
				'Submit'
			)
		),
		RequiredFields::create(....)
	);

	$validation = JQueryValidation::create($form);

### JQueryValidation->generate()
For automated creation use:

	// then you can either use automated creation like this:
	// this will inspect all form fields and add their validation methods.
	// It also will add required checks provided by form's RequiredFields.
	$validation->generate();

	// It is also possible to provide custom error messages and behaviour through passing a config array like this:
	$validation->generate(array(
		'messages' => array(
			'CheckboxField_DATA' => array(
				'required' => 'Custom message'
			)
		)
	));
	// Expected hooks are messages, rules, groups.

### JQueryValidation->custom()
If you want to provide your own validation file you can use this:

	$validation->custom('path/to/your.js');

	// It is also possible to provide information about which additional js files shoul be loaded, like this:
	$validation->custom(
		'path/to/your.js',
		array(
			'additionalMethods' => true,
			'metaData' => true,
			'moment' => true
		)
	);

